-- Kenya Power Shares Post Biggest Gain in Almost Two Months
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2012-02-23T13:52:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/kenya-power-shares-post-biggest-gain-in-almost-two-months-1-.html
Kenya Power & Lighting Ltd. (KPLL) , the
East African nation’s sole electricity distributor, posted its
largest gain in almost two months in Nairobi.  The stock jumped as much as 6.3 percent and closed 3.4
percent stronger at 16.55 shillings, marking the biggest gain
since Dec. 27. The volume of shares traded was 663,700, more
than triple the three-month average.  Kestrel Capital East Africa Ltd., a Nairobi-based
brokerage, yesterday maintained its “long-term buy” on the
stock with a price estimate of 22 shillings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Paul Richardson  in Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 